This is a simple command-line application for macOS that will take an
ICS (iCal) feed (passed as argument), locate entries with summary "You
{exited,entered} work", calculate their time difference and present a
daily and weekly summary of your work hours.

It is intended to be used with this IFTTT applet which lets you
automatically save calendar entries based on your iOS device
geolocation:

  https://ifttt.com/applets/ud7hrSuw-track-your-work-hours-in-ios-calendar

It depends on libical being installed in /usr/local/lib (available in
Homebrew).